comments.body:
@ekzp This cmdlet is just a thin wrapper around the .NET SMTP client API which has other known issues and deprecated.  We also continue to ship `Send-MailMessage` for compatibility reasons for existing scripts.  It looks like there are at least 3 modules on PowerShellGallery already using MailKit https://www.powershellgallery.com/packages?q=mailkit.  I'm not personally endorsing any of them as i haven't used them nor have a need for this type of functionality, but I do suggest moving off of `Send-MailMessage`.

<blockquote><img src="/favicon.ico" width="48" align="right"><div><strong><a href="https://www.powershellgallery.com/packages?q=mailkit">PowerShell Gallery
        | Packages matching mailkit</a></strong></div></blockquote>
